By teaching several languages, especially in developing countries, children will have better opportunities for meaningful employment.
In Scotland, each school varies according to the languages they teach.
A number of schools focus on more classical modern languages, while others teach languages that are considered the most important for the UK, looking to the future of 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Whatever your child's interests are, there will always be many languages to choose from in an independent school with teaching staff and professionals in the field.
Scottish independent schools are ready to create a teaching environment that will prepare children and equip them with the necessary skills to live in the future.
It is undeniable that, in today's global business environment, languages remain vital to the future of the country, so it is also necessary to reflect this in the education system.
Indeed, modern languages should certainly be considered "international communication skills".
Independent schools will continue to offer this opportunity for choice, diversity and results to Scottish youth.
This must be done.
